comment:
* A representation of an search target event.
 *
 * There are two types of events. First type of event correspends to the user interaction
 * that happens on the search surface. (e.g., {@link #ACTION_TAP}. Second type of events
 * correspends to the lifecycle event of the search surface {@link #ACTION_SURFACE_VISIBLE}.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: FLAG_IME_SHOWN
variables.comment: * IME was shown when event happened.

variables.name: ACTION_TAP
variables.comment: * Constants that define tapping without closing the search surface.

variables.name: ACTION_LONGPRESS
variables.comment: * Constants that define long pressing without closing the search surface.

variables.name: ACTION_LAUNCH_TOUCH
variables.comment: * Constants that define tapping on the touch target to launch.

variables.name: ACTION_LAUNCH_KEYBOARD_FOCUS
variables.comment: * Constants that define tapping on the soft keyboard confirm or search to launch.

variables.name: ACTION_DRAGNDROP
variables.comment: * Searcheable item was draged and dropped to another surface.

variables.name: ACTION_DELETE
variables.comment: * Constant that defines user deleted a target.

variables.name: ACTION_DISMISS
variables.comment: * Constant that defines user dismissed a target.

methods.name: public String getTargetId()
methods.comment: * Returns the primary search target with interaction.

methods.name: public List<String> getTargetIds()
methods.comment: * Returns the list of search targets with visualization change.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
